&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary People Partner presence for Japan &amp;amp; APAC - the first point of contact for leaders across levels, functions, and markets, bringing local context &amp;amp; understanding, and regional business understanding to your partnerships&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with functional People Partners to support the continued scaling of the teams in region by evolving team structures, roles, and operating models in line with business growth. Serve as the regional connector between functional People Partners and regional business leaders&amp;nbsp; - translating global people priorities into locally relevant solutions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coach senior leaders to strengthen leadership capability, team effectiveness, and performance in a high-growth, target-driven environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and address organisational friction points by improving cross-functional alignment and operational clarity across teams, proactively surface and embed regional context in your work with partners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Embed as a key partner across cross-functional stakeholders, including functional People Partners, Compensation, Recruiting, Learning &amp;amp; Development, BEI, and People Relations, to drive and deliver high-impact people initiatives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage data, organisational insights, and employee feedback to proactively inform decisions and drive measurable improvements in team health, effectiveness, and performance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and drive a Japan &amp;amp; APAC people strategy that reflects both the region&#39;s stage of growth and its commercial priorities - balancing the need to build scalable people foundations across multiple markets with strong alignment to the global GTM pillar and broader Figma people strategy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Explore and embed AI tools and approaches that extend your reach and impact across the region - whether through smarter use of people analytics, scaled manager enablement, or more efficient ways of working - and share learnings with the broader People Partner team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
