&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Figma is growing our team of passionate creatives and builders on a mission to make design accessible to all. Figma’s platform helps teams bring ideas to life—whether you&#39;re brainstorming, creating a prototype, translating designs into code, or iterating with AI. From idea to product, Figma empowers teams to streamline workflows, move faster, and work together in real time from anywhere in the world. If you&#39;re excited to shape the future of design and collaboration, join us!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Figma is hiring a Director of Communications to help us set a new standard for corporate communications at a public company. We aren’t looking to build upon the standard corporate comms playbook; we’re looking to reimagine it from first principles. Successful candidates will go beyond simply setting strategy to define a new model for how public companies communicate, partnering across the company — finance, investor relations, legal, brand studio, product and design — to mine and tell stories that drive conversation across audiences, formats and channels.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role calls for range. You should be as comfortable in a spreadsheet as you are on X/Twitter. You’re capable of crafting campaigns around quarterly earnings and cultural moments. You speak the language of finance and know what it takes to translate it for a broader audience without dumbing it down. You embrace ambiguity, are collaborative by default, and are energized by the chance to lead a team and build something new.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full-time role based in San Francisco or New York City hubs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do at Figma:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and drive Figma’s corporate storytelling strategy end-to-end, from narrative development to execution across channels&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Move beyond traditional PR to create integrated campaigns that cut through across media, owned platforms and executive communications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with cross-functional teams to translate business and financial momentum into clear, compelling stories and campaigns&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with executives to shape narratives that resonate with business and financial audiences, from briefings to thought leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and develop breakthrough story angles that position Figma at the center of key industry and market conversations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and deepen relationships with top-tier business and financial reporters across the U.S. and U.K.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay close to the news cycle while proactively creating opportunities that put Figma ahead of it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continue to grow your scope and influence as the company scales&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’d love to hear from you if you have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;12+ years of experience in in-house corporate communications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A track record of building and scaling communications programs and teams from the ground up&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong business and financial fluency, with the ability to translate complexity into clear, engaging narratives, and pitches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience operating in fast-paced environments where direction isn’t always defined—and comfort creating it&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience crafting a point of view on storytelling that goes beyond conventional PR approaches&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;While not required, it’s an added plus if you also have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An understanding of product design, software development and/or cloud-native applications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
