&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Figma is growing our team of passionate creatives and builders on a mission to make design accessible to all. Figma’s platform helps teams bring ideas to life—whether you&#39;re brainstorming, creating a prototype, translating designs into code, or iterating with AI. From idea to product, Figma empowers teams to streamline workflows, move faster, and work together in real time from anywhere in the world. If you&#39;re excited to shape the future of design and collaboration, join us!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;section page-centered&quot;&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re building the next chapter of AI-native craft and creativity - where craft and technology meet. Figma Weave platform bridges the gap between AI capabilities and human creativity, and lets professional creatives and designers harness the power of the world’s leading AI models without losing precision, expression, or soul.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re seeking a Community Manager to cultivate and energize our artist community—the core of our mission. In this hands-on, people-first role, you’ll manage our daily presence on Discord, bringing our Collective, community programs, and creative partnerships to life through events, collaborations, and meaningful engagement. You’ll connect with artists, educators, and creators who use Weavy, ensuring they feel supported and inspired, while channeling their feedback into ideas that shape and strengthen the platform.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full time role that can be held from our New York Hub.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do at Figma Weave:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and evolve the community growth model - programming cadence, tier structures, health metrics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage day-to-day life in Discord - moderation, updates, events, and user feedback loops&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan and host activities like challenges, workshops, and live sessions (aligned with Collective and education programs)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and support collaborations with schools, creative artists, and studios; coordinate co-branded sessions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain resource libraries, onboarding materials, and event follow-ups to help members get the most out of Weavy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the community artists - support spotlight content, track participation, and celebrate community work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Capture insights from the community and share them with the product and marketing teams to inform roadmap and communications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We’d love to hear from you if you have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6+ years of experience building and scaling engaged online communities - from early stages to thriving ecosystems, ideally in creative tech, design tools, or GenAI spaces&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on expertise with Discord (or similar platforms), including structuring channels, moderating discussions, and fostering authentic community culture&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communicator in English with the ability to write clearly, host conversations, and confidently represent our creative tone&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;People-first and collaborative, who can build a close partnership with marketing, product, and creative teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactive and organized builder who thrives in fast-paced environments, managing multiple projects and taking ideas from concept to execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in running and executing community events, hosting a workshops is a big plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;While not required, it’s an added plus if you also have:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background in design, education, or creator programs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
